column1: That took us quite a while.

It was only because you were all with me.
But I do wonder if Mari-san will be okay...

I'd say so. Her Shadow disappeared like they
always do.

Yeah, your feelings definitely reached her.
I'm sure her heart has changed for the better.
I guess this wraps up the mission.

We still need to confirm that the citizens are all
back to normal. It'd be nice if we could do that
right away...

Can't we grab somethin' to eat first? I'm hungry
enough to pass out here.

He has a point. Battles can't be fought on an
empty stomach.
The battle's already over, but still...

Hey... Can we try jingisukan—that delicious
lamb barbecue dish!?
Ooh, that's a must in Hokkaido!

What!? I thought we were finally getting lobster
hot pot...

Since when did we decide that? And why would
we, when it's so damn hot out?

But if you think about it, isn't jingisukan
also sorta like hot pot?
No way! Isn't it supposed to be barbecue?

Well, cooking jingisukan does require a utensil
called a jingisukan pot... and you can't barbecue
in a pot.
Then it really is hot pot.

Hah, I figured as much. Then to lobster hot pot
we go!
Why? What even is this conversation?

Right? You cook it just like barbecue, so...
Wait, what were we talking about?

True. Though sukiyaki is served hot pot style,
its etymology does refer to grilling. I wonder
why.
Hey! Was that a smile just now?

Yeah! Straight from Sapporo, it's Beauty
Thief's award-winning smile!

I'm relieved too. I thought you might be
weighed down by all that's happened.

Indeed, she was so weighed down that she met
up with our leader for a private midnight chat.

Mwehehe... All right, Sophia. Find us the best
jingisukan in Sapporo!
Ah, sorry. Okay, I've got it.

I can feel a strong bond with my
friends...
